The primary focus of the Computer Science - Games Technology (with foundation year) BSc (Hons) course at Clifton Campus is to provide students with a unique blend of computer science and specialized games technology modules. This combination equips students with a strong foundation in both theoretical and practical aspects of computing, while also developing their creativity and problem-solving skills in the context of game development.

The curriculum and modules of this course are designed to prepare students for diverse career opportunities in creative applications of computer technology. For instance, students learn programming, mathematics, and computer graphics, which are essential skills for game development. Additionally, they gain experience in areas such as game design, animation, and artificial intelligence, which are increasingly important in the gaming industry.

